name: 04 - Model Training and Evaluation
content:
Customer Segmentation â€“ Clustering

Method: H2O KMeans clustering on household demographics and transactional behavior.

Results:

  • Cluster 0: Low-activity, low-coupon usage, price-insensitive shoppers.
  • Cluster 1: High-value, promotion-sensitive shoppers with frequent coupon use and heavy spending.
  • Cluster 2: Similar to Cluster 1 but with stronger private-label preference and in-store discount responsiveness.

Insights:

Clusters 1 and 2 represent prime targets for tailored promotions and cross-sell strategies, while Cluster 0 indicates households requiring different engagement tactics or cost-conscious targeting.

Coupon Redemption â€“ Predictive Modeling

Method: H2O XGBoost Classifier trained on transaction + household features.

Feature Importances:

  1. Average Price per Transaction â€“ strongest predictor of coupon redemption.
  2. Total Visits / Frequency â€“ high-visit households show greater redemption likelihood.
  3. Median Basket Size â€“ larger basket households are more responsive.
  4. Discount Sensitivity Index â€“ secondary driver.
  5. Demographics (age, income, household size): weaker influence compared to behavioral features.

Model Metrics:

  • High AUC-ROC, indicating strong separation between redeemers and non-redeemers.
  • Balanced Precision/Recall, ensuring effective targeting without excessive false positives.
